<HEADLINE> Nursing Home Aide Sentenced  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SALEM, Mass. (AP) -- A former nursing home aide who raped and impregnated a
comatose patient has been sentenced to 11 years in prison.
</P>
<P>
	   Israel Moret pleaded guilty to rape and abusing a patient in a long-term
care facility. The woman later gave birth prematurely to a baby who suffered
severe brain damage. The baby needs round-the-clock care just as her mother
does.
</P>
<P>
	   ``Our family now has a second broken child because of what he did,'' the
victim's sister said Friday in court. ``He has sentenced our family to sorrow
for life. Our hearts sink when we hold her, hear the machines that keep her
alive, and anticipate her future.''
</P>
<P>
	   The victim was a 24-year-old resident of Town Manor Nursing and
Rehabilitation Center in Lawrence when her pregnancy was discovered in October
1998. Police used DNA analysis to identify Moret as the father.
</P>
<P>
	   Moret's lawyer, Lawrence McGuire, said his client wanted to apologize to the
victim's family.
</P>
<P>
	   ``He has also told me to tell this court and all who will listen that he
expects to do what he can for this child,'' McGuire said.
</P>
</TEXT>
