<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000212.0067 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-12 02:40 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jet Lands in Phoenix With Problem  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX (AP) -- A TWA jet similar to the type involved in the recent Alaska
Airlines crash experienced hydraulic problems before landing Friday night at Sky
Harbor International Airport.
</P>
<P>
	   The MD-80 landed safely and the 149 people aboard were taken off without any
problems, airport spokeswoman Suzanne Luber said. TWA said Flight 299 was en
route to Phoenix from St. Louis.
</P>
<P>
	   Luber said she didn't know the nature of the problem but that the plane's
pilot had radioed that the jet had hydraulic failure and requested an emergency
landing.
</P>
<P>
	   However, TWA spokesman Jim Brown said ``there was no emergency declared. It
was a minor hydraulic problem.''
</P>
<P>
	   An Alaska Airlines MD-83 crashed Jan. 31 off the coast of California,
killing all 88 people aboard. The Federal Aviation Administration this week
ordered all planes in the MD-80 series inspected.
</P>
<P>
	   Whether the TWA plane had been inspected wasn't immediately known. Also
unclear was the nature of the hydraulics problem.
</P>
<P>
	   Luber and Brown said TWA officials would investigate.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-02-12-00 0240 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000212.0068 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-12 02:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Shot at Isley Brothers Concert  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- One person was shot to death and three others were
wounded at an Isley Brothers concert late Friday, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
	   The shooting at the Los Angeles Sports Arena was reported shortly before 11
p.m., said Officer Don Cox, a police spokesman. The Isley Brothers -- known for
such hits as ``It's Your Thing'' and ``That Lady'' -- were performing at the
time.
</P>
<P>
	   Fire Department spokesman Bob Collis confirmed the fatality. He also said
one of the wounded was critically hurt and the others had minor injuries.
</P>
</TEXT>
