<HEADLINE> Former Miss America Gets Big Break  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- A former Miss America has gotten her big break on Broadway.
</P>
<P>
	   Miss America 1998 Kate Shindle has been the understudy for the lead female
role in the musical "Jekyll &AMP; Hyde" since the beginning of the year. She had
been waiting tables at Artie's, a delicatessen at 82nd and Broadway, but quit
when she landed a part in the show's chorus after auditioning in December.
</P>
<P>
	   Shindle, 23, took the stage as a star for the first time Wednesday after
Coleen Sexton, who normally plays the part of Lucy, a doomed prostitute, called
out sick.
</P>
<P>
	   The former Miss Illinois told the New York Post her Miss America title and
the publicity about her waitressing job probably helped jumpstart her acting
career.
</P>
<P>
	   "It provided the entry spark," she said. "But I'm not so jaded as to think
that it's the only reason I got the part. They put me through the paces at the
audition."
</P>
</TEXT>
