<HEADLINE> Phone prankster pretends to be 'Millionaire' host  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
    	   PALMYRA, N.Y. (AP) - Who wants to be a numskull?
<P>
	   A teen-ager who masqueraded as "Who Wants to be a Millionaire?" host Regis
Philbin in a prank telephone call was arrested soon afterward and charged with
aggravated harassment. His phone number showed up on the victim's Caller ID box,
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
	   The 17-year-old boy was accused of making a phone call last week from his
home in Palmyra, 25 miles east of Rochester, and identifying himself as the host
of the popular television game show.
</P>
<P>
	   The woman he called said she was told that if she answered a few questions
correctly, she would be a contestant on the show. When she answered the
questions, she said the teen then hurled abuse at her and hung up.
</P>
