<HEADLINE> Report: Israel Heightens Security  </HEADLINE>
   By LAURIE COPANS Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) -- Israel put security forces on alert around the country
Saturday due to intelligence reports that terror attacks could be carried out in
crowded places, Israel radio reported.
</P>
<P>
	   Security forces increased their numbers in many cities in reaction to the
warning, which was not specific about a time or place, the radio said. Police
officials did not immediately return phone calls to comment on the report.
</P>
<P>
	   Israeli security officials arrested on Saturday the head of the Islamic
movement at a university in the West Bank city of Ramallah and three other
Palestinians near Bethlehem, Israel army radio reported.
</P>
<P>
	   The army spokesman's office refused to comment on the army radio report.
</P>
<P>
	   It was unclear if the attack warning was related to a recent stalemate in
peace talks with the Palestinians over a disagreement regarding Israeli
withdrawals from the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
	   Palestinian International Cooperation Minister Nabil Shaath said Friday that
security coordination was ongoing with Israel despite the crisis in the
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
	   Palestinian police have arrested eight Palestinians since Thursday for
alleged involvement in a car explosion near the West Bank city of Nablus that
Palestinian security officials said was an attempt to carry out a terror attack
in Israel.
</P>
<P>
	   One Palestinian was killed and another injured in the explosion, the
Palestinian security officials said on condition of anonymity. Three of the
suspects were later released.
</P>
<P>
	   Israeli security officials said on condition of anonymity that the warning
of possible attacks came in light of information the Palestinians had extracted
from the suspects in the car explosion.
</P>
<P>
	   Some of those Palestinians arrested were allegedly members of the Islamic
resistance group Hamas, which has carried out several deadly attacks in Israel
but has not succeeded in carrying out any major attacks in several months.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
