have caused the Alaskan Airlines crash two weeks ago. Since Thursday, 21 planes
have been found to have irregularities with tail wing jackscrews, the
2-foot-long rods that drive the stabilizers that keep planes level, the Federal
Aviation Administration and airlines said. Most airlines said their companies
had completed most of the required inspections and expected to have the job
finished by Sunday morning.
